	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Western Cape police say a man from Bishop Lavis was shot and killed around 11:00 on Friday. "This morning at around 11:00 an adult male from Bishop Lavis was shot and killed in Voortrekker Road in Kensington by unknown suspects who fled the scene in a white Mercedes Vito," Lieutenant Colonel Andrè Traut told News24. Police are still investigating the circumstances around the incident. Eyewitness News earlier reported that the man was a passenger on a bus that was en route to Maitland cemetery. "Golden Arrow can confirm a fatal shooting incident earlier on 21 September which took place on a private hire near Maitland cemetery. The exact circumstances are not yet clear," spokesperson Bronwen Dyke-Beyer told Eyewitness News. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  